casebody.data:
PEOPLE of the State of Michigan, Plaintiff-Appellee,
v.
Willie Eddie ANDERSON, II, Defendant-Appellant. SC: 156906
COA: 331466 Supreme Court of Michigan. June 5, 2019

Order

On order of the Court, the motion to withdraw issue is GRANTED. The motion to file an in pro per supplement to the application for leave to appeal and the motion to accept the in pro per motion to remand are GRANTED. The application for leave to appeal the October 19, 2017 judgment of the Court of Appeals is considered, and it is DENIED, because we are not persuaded that the questions presented should be reviewed by this Court. The motion to remand is DENIED.
